∴ AEONMI Quantum-Native Syntax Example
∵ This demonstrates the unique AEONMI programming paradigm

∴ Quantum variable declarations
⟨quantum_state⟩ ∈ |0⟩ + |1⟩              ∴ Superposition binding
⟨classical_var⟩ ← 42                      ∴ Classical binding  
⟨tensor_data⟩ ⊗ [1, 2, 3]                 ∴ Tensor array
⟨approx_value⟩ ≈ 3.14159                  ∴ Approximate binding

∴ Quantum functions
◯ classical_add⟨a, b⟩ → ⟨result⟩ {
    ⟨result⟩ ← ⟨a⟩ + ⟨b⟩
}

⊙ quantum_superpose⟨q⟩ {
    𓀀⟨q⟩                                  ∴ Hadamard gate
}

🧠 neural_process⟨input⟩ → ⟨output⟩ {
    ⟨hidden⟩ ← 𝒩⟨input⟩
    ⟨output⟩ ← ⟨hidden⟩
}

∴ Probability-based control flow
⊖ ⟨quantum_state⟩ ≈ 0.7 ⇒ {
    ∴ 70% probability branch
    log("Quantum measurement: |0⟩")
} ⊕ {
    ∴ 30% probability branch  
    log("Quantum measurement: |1⟩")
}

∴ Quantum loop with decoherence
⟨counter⟩ ← 0
⟲ ⟨counter⟩ ⪰ 5 ⇒ {
    ⟨counter⟩ ← ⟨counter⟩ + 1
    𓀀⟨quantum_state⟩
}

∴ Quantum try-catch with error probability
⚡ {
    ⟨risky_result⟩ ← quantum_operation⟨quantum_state⟩
} ⚠️ ⟨error⟩ ≈ 0.1 ⇒ {
    log("Quantum decoherence detected!")
} ✓ {
    log("Quantum operation successful!")
}

∴ Multi-dimensional quantum arrays
⟨qmatrix⟩ ∇ [2×3×4]
⟨qmatrix⟩⟦0, 1, 2⟧ ← |+⟩

∴ AI learning block
🧠 learn {
    ⟨training_data⟩ ⊗ quantum_dataset
    ⟨model⟩ ← gradient_descent⟨training_data⟩
}

∴ Time-bounded quantum operations
⏰ duration⟨500ms⟩ ⇒ {
    ⟨coherent_state⟩ ∈ maintain_coherence⟨quantum_state⟩
}